      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be directly relevant to the hemolysis prediction decision in the COU.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) are the primary regulatory QoIs for CPB device submissions. Both are computed directly from the CFD stress-exposure integral and are the quantities compared against the predicate device. Relevance to COU decision is direct and unambiguous."
    },
    {
